msgstr "/glark/, 他動詞"

#: ../../G/glark.rst:9
msgid ""
"To figure something out from context. \"The System III manuals are pretty "
"poor, but you can generally glark the meaning from context.\" Interestingly,"
" the word was originally ‘glork’; the context was \"This gubblick contains "
"many nonsklarkish English flutzpahs, but the overall pluggandisp can be "
"glorked [sic] from context\" (David Moser, quoted by Douglas Hofstadter in "
"his *Metamagical Themas* column in the January 1981 *Scientific "
"American*\\). It is conjectured that hacker usage mutated the verb to "
"‘glark’ because :ref:`glork` was already an established jargon term (some "
"hackers do report using the original term). Compare :ref:`grok`\\, "
":ref:`zen`\\."
msgstr ""
"文脈から何かを理解すること。「System "
"IIIのマニュアルはかなりお粗末だが、たいていは文脈から意味をglarkできる。」興味深いことに、この語は元々‘glork’だった。その文脈は「This"
" gubblick contains many nonsklarkish English flutzpahs, but the overall "
"pluggandisp can be glorked [sic] from context」だった(David Moserの言葉、Douglas "
"Hofstadterが1981年1月の *Scientific American* の彼のコラム *Metamagical Themas* "
"で引用)。\\ :ref:`glork`\\ "
"がすでに確立されたジャーゴンの用語だったため、ハッカーの用法が動詞を‘glark’に変異させたと推測される(一部のハッカーは元の用語を使っていると報告している)。\\"
" :ref:`grok`\\ 、\\ :ref:`zen`\\ と比較せよ。"
